<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-81-0444 </DOCNO><TEXT>The availability of natural gas in India and an increasing productionfrom the Bombay High and Gujaret areas is encouraging the developmentof an infrastructure to capture offshore gas for feedstocks and bothindustrial and domestic fuels. An estimated 478 billion cubic metersof gas reserves could produce the equivalent of 43 million tons of oildaily. The author reviews several options for developing nations basedon a demand survey for fertilizer, fuels, and power and transport asa way to substitute natural gas for oil and other energy sources. Heconcludes that gas could eventually surpass oil as a primary fuel. 1figure, 6 tables.</TEXT></DOC>